    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-08-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-08-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="768"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d768">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">701.0090/1927: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-28">August 28,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2105. American interests Far East—exchange. Your 5301, August 27.<note n="7"
                        xml:id="d768fn7">Not printed.</note> Please inform Gorgé and Fontanel<note
                        n="8" xml:id="d768fn8">Emile Fontanel, Swiss Consul General at
                        Shanghai.</note> that each child is counted as a person for purposes of
                    American-Japanese exchange. This is necessary in view of the need of keeping the
                    ship’s company within the limits of the certified lifeboat capacity of the <hi
                        rend="italic">Gripsholm</hi>. The proposal that children under 2 years be
                    not counted and those between 2 and 4 years be counted as half persons was made
                    by the British Government in connection with the British-Japanese exchange and
                    is not applicable to the American-Japanese exchange.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
